<p>What do you mean with the setRightRumbleDriver, what is that? And how do i configure my xbox controller to get the HID? Is it the POV value? Also one last question, to configure so it could detect either the apriltag below speaker at blue/left side, how do you tell it to do it?</p>
<p>Sorry for making some questions, its my first time programming something using vision <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/frowning.png?v=12" title=":frowning:" class="emoji" alt=":frowning:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2024-03-11T00:22:28.522Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":7,"reads":128,"readers_count":127,"score":65.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":458163,"topic_slug":"swerve-drive-yagsl-w-limelight-autoposition-help","display_username":"Emmanuel Perez","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":51481,"username":"dylan292","name":"Dylan","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dylan292/{size}/168044_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":61412,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/swerve-drive-yagsl-w-limelight-autoposition-help/458163/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3329690,"name":"Dylan","username":"dylan292","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dylan292/{size}/168044_2.png","created_at":"2024-03-11T05:14:56.213Z","cooked":"<p>It’s an optional thing I put in out code. I designed it so if we don’t have a vision target and we are trying to align to one, it will vibrate the controller. This lets the driver know the robot can’t auto align.</p>
<p>I’m not sure what HID is exactly, just that I needed to get it to vibrate the controller.</p>
<p>Finally you can change what target you select with. <code>SwerveSub.setVisionTargetID(aprilTagIDNum);</code></p>
<p>The docs for it is here <a href="https://docs.limelightvision.io/docs/docs-limelight/apis/complete-networktables-api" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Complete NetworkTables API | Limelight Documentation</a></p>
<p><code>priorityid | SET the required ID for tx/ty targeting. Ignore other targets. Does not affect localization</code></p>
<p>I still need to implement this, but you can have something that select what ID should be given based off what alliance <span class="abbreviation">FMS<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Field Management System"></template></span> says you are on using <code>DriverStation.getAlliance();</code></p>
<p>Something like this in the initialization of the command.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">if(DriverStation.getAlliance() == DriverStation.Alliance.Red){
      SwerveSub.setVisionTargetID(AprilTagIDforRedSpeaker)
}else{
     SwerveSub.setVisionTargetID(AprilTagIDforBlueSpeaker)
}
</code></pre>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2024-03-11T05:14:56.213Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":13,"reads":98,"readers_count":97,"score":89.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":458163,"topic_slug":"swerve-drive-yagsl-w-limelight-autoposition-help","display_username":"Dylan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.limelightvision.io/docs/docs-limelight/apis/complete-networktables-api","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Complete NetworkTables API | Limelight Documentation","clicks":12}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":61412,"username":"Emma4735","name":"Emmanuel Perez","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/emma4735/{size}/216176_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":51481,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/swerve-drive-yagsl-w-limelight-autoposition-help/458163/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3329699,"name":"Emmanuel Perez","username":"Emma4735","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/emma4735/{size}/216176_2.png","created_at":"2024-03-11T05:53:39.437Z","cooked":"<p>Thankss!!! And is there another way to activate the command with a button for example?</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2024-03-11T05:53:39.437Z","reply_count":0,"reply_t